The '''''Symphony in B-Flat Major ("Mannheim No. 3")''''' is a Mannheim symphony by [[Johann Stamitz]], probably written sometime from 1741 to 1746.<ref>{{cite web|title=Notes to Johann Stamitz Symphonies Vol. 1 on Naxos|url=http://www.naxos.com/mainsite/blurbs_reviews.asp?item_code=8.553194&catNum=553194&filetype=About%20this%20Recording&language=English#|accessdate=19 September 2009}}</ref> It might be Stamitz' first symphony. It is formed in the standard 3-movement symphonic scheme of the time: #Alla Breve #Andante #Allegro
This symphony, just like the others by Stamitz, definitely influenced [[Joseph Haydn]] and [[Mozart]]. It is about 8 minutes long.
==See also== *[[Symphony in G major "Mannheim No. 1" (Stamitz)]] *[[Symphony in A major "Mannheim No. 2" (Stamitz)]]
